- For individual language names this article uses the ALMG orthographies for the Mayan languages of Guatemala, and the Mexican languages Ch'ol, Wastek and Tojolab'al. Traditional Spanish spellings are used for Tzotzil, Tzeltal, Lacand<U+00F3>n and Chicomuceltec. The Cordemex orthography is used for the Yucatec language. For Classical Quich<U+00E9> the traditional spanish spelling is used. The name Jakaltek is preferred over the alternative Popti'.
- For the names of language groups in the genealogical classification the following spellings are used: Ch'olan, Q'anjobalan, Quichean, Yucatecan and Huastecan.-->
